subproject.corporate outcome: Strengthened national capacity for inclusive governance and coordination of national HIV responses, and for the protection of human rights of people affected by HIV, including women and other vulnerable groups
subproject.description: The program is aimed to strengthen the national partners’ activities to effectively tackle the issues of HIV/AIDS and Occupational Safety Health (OSH) at the formal and informal sectors through having dedicated leadership, knowledgeable trainers, strong OSH and HIV/AIDS Unit and committees, well-organized training and documentation centre, and well-tailored HIV/AIDS and OSH programmes at all levels.
